# .trivyignore — Trivy config-scan allowlist with mandatory rationale per rule.
#
# Doctrine R-3 (no `|| true` masking): blanket suppressions are forbidden;
# per-rule entries WITH inline context are acceptable security hygiene.
# Each entry below MUST justify why the finding is either a false positive
# or a known gap tracked under a REMEDIATION ticket.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS-0164 — Subnet associates public IP address.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# False positive: `aws_subnet.public` (terraform/main.tf:35-42) is INTENDED
# public-facing. The `map_public_ip_on_launch = true` setting is the
# conventional AWS pattern for public subnets that host the ALB, NAT Gateway,
# and bastion host. Application workloads (ECS tasks, RDS instances) live in
# `aws_subnet.private` and are NOT exposed to the public internet — egress to
# the public network is gated through the NAT Gateway in the public subnet.
# Real workloads are scheduled into the private subnet via Terraform's
# subnet_ids variable on each compute resource.
AWS-0164

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AWS-0079 — Cluster does not specify a customer managed key for storage
# encryption.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Acknowledged gap, tracked under R-ECS-CMK-001 (W3, REMEDIATION § 7).
# Both `aws_ecs_cluster.app` (terraform/main.tf:113) and `aws_ecs_cluster.this`
# (terraform/modules/k8s/main.tf:36) lack
# `configuration { execute_command_configuration { kms_key_id = ... } }`.
# The rule fires because the execute-command log encryption is unspecified.
# Mitigating factors: execute_command itself is NOT enabled on these clusters
# at v1.0 deployment scale (no `enable_execute_command = true` on any task
# definition); without execute_command, there are no command logs to encrypt.
# When execute_command is enabled (Tier 4 SaaS troubleshooting need), the
# KMS key reference will be wired in the same change. R-ECS-CMK-001 covers
# the proactive wiring against the existing R-RDS-KMS-001 KMS key so the
# cluster is encryption-ready before execute_command is opted into.
AWS-0079
